[assistant] Refined the dedicated `Routine` coverage test and amended the commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change added:
[assistant] - `resolvesAndInvokesLibraryJavaFunctionDeclaredThroughSql()`
[assistant]   - Declares and invokes an HSQLDB Java routine backed by `java.lang.Math.abs`.
[assistant]   - Uses a rejecting context classloader so `Routine.getMethods()` exercises both:
[assistant]     - `Class.forName(String, boolean, ClassLoader)`
[assistant]     - fallback `Class.forName(String)`
[assistant]   - Uses a library/JDK target instead of only test helper methods, making the reflective routine resolution path more robust for dynamic-access coverage.
[assistant] 
